Package io.honeycomb.libhoney.responses

Classes that define different types of responses that can be received for a submitted event. Users can register a ResponseObserver to view these responses.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ClientRejected
    A response indicating that the event was rejected on the client-side and was never sent to the server.
    Response
    Common type for all responses from the HoneyClient, which can be consumed via the ResponseObserver.
    ServerAccepted
    Marker for event responses that were accepted by the honeycomb server.
    ServerRejected
    Marker for event responses that have were rejected by the honeycomb server.
    ServerResponse
    Supertype for event responses that have reached the honeycomb server and therefore have an associated HTTP response.
    ServerResponse.BatchData
    For batched events this will contain data about the the batch response as a whole.
    Unknown
    An event response with unknown outcome.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ResponseObservable
    Maintains a collection of registered ResponseObservers and publishes responses to them.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ClientRejected.RejectionReason  
    Unknown.ReasonType
